This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on improving neural machine translation. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an extension to a state-of-the-art model using machine learning techniques. Furthermore, the paper may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of AI algorithms to improve translation performance. The paper may also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks to improve translation quality. Finally, the paper may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves the use of character-level models, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
